The paper deals with designing lower bounds on the competitive ratio in the online setting, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The techniques used involve linear programming duality, which is a common tool in optimization and game theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
